news.title: In a first, Mivan technology to be used for PMAY homes in Udham Singh Nagar
news.para: ​The technique, used for the first time in government schemes in the state, eliminates the need for traditional bricks and reduces labour requirements.

news.title: Bank of Canada urges removal of barriers to home building to cut inflation
news.para: Deputy governor Toni Gravelle spoke a day after the central bank held its key overnight rate at 5% but left the door open to another hike, saying it was still concerned about inflation.

news.title: Karnataka government tables bill in assembly proposing hike in stamp duty
news.para: ​The bill titled The Karnataka Stamp (Amendment) Bill, 2023 was tabled in the Assembly by Rural Development Minister Priyank Kharge on behalf of Revenue Minister Krishna Byre Gowda.

news.title: China: Shimao Group trades flat after issuing plan to revamp offshore debt
news.para: Shimao Group, with around $11.7 billion in offshore notes, bonds and other credit facilities has been pushing forward plans to revamp its debts over the past few months, Shimao said in a filing to the Hong Kong Stock Exchange late on Thursday.

news.title: RBI retains repo rate at 6.5% for fifth time in a row
news.para: Announcing the bi-monthly monetary policy, RBI Governor Shaktikanta Das said the Monetary Policy Committee (MPC) unanimously decided to keep the repo rate unchanged at 6.5 per cent.

news.title: Prayagraj civic body issues 'red notice' to over 7,000 house tax defaulters
news.para: Of these, 2,433 have an outstanding of more than Rs 1 lakh. If these defaulters fail to deposit the dues within a given time, action will be taken to attach and seal their building. There are a total of 2.32 lakh buildings in the municipal corporation (except extended areas).

news.title: Land identified for Tidel park in Nilgiris: Tamil Nadu tourism minister
news.para: After inspecting the site, the minister said that a proposal in this regard would soon be sent to the government. The setting up of a Tidel park in the Nilgiris was one of the election promises made by the DMK.

news.title: Goa: GIDC notifies revised plot allotment regulations to attract new investment
news.para: The new norms have introduced a marking system for plot allotment, which gives additional points for women entrepreneurs, local entrepreneurs, start-ups, patent holders and sustainability measures.

news.title: Has Bengaluru development body lost the plot on Kempegowda Layout story?
news.para: BDA fails to provide basic amenities at one of its well-known layouts, misses 4 deadlines and now stands accused of having provided wrong info in Assembly

news.title: Delhi court initiates process to declare Nivas Promoters' director "absconder"
news.para: Metropolitan Magistrate Vinod Joshi noted that the non-bailable warrants (NBWs) issued against Rahul Chamola, the Director of 'Nivas Promoters Pvt Ltd', was received back unexecuted with the report that he was not found at the given address.

news.title: Central government amends rules to allow demarcation of non-processing area under IT SEZs
news.para: According to the new amendment the board of approval, on request of a developer of an Information Technology or Information Technology enabled services Special Economic Zones (SEZ), may, permit demarcation of a portion of the built-up area as a non-processing area.

news.title: Hyderabad: All 50 criminal cases related to Sahiti Infra moved to CCS
news.para: ​This includes 50 different criminal cases related to the firm and its managing director Lakshmi Narayana, who are accused of cheating hundreds of people by falsely promising to sell residential and commercial space to them in their different projects.

news.title: Delhi government mulls stipend for construction workers affected by GRAP curbs
news.para: There are around a lakh workers registered with the Delhi government who are beneficiaries of various welfare schemes, the officials said.

news.title: To reduce straw burning, Punjab government urges brick kiln owners to use 20% stubble
news.para: During the meetings at Punjab Bhawan here, the minister urged the brick-kiln and crusher owners and the mining contractors to support the government in its endeavour to bring transparency in the mining sector and tackle paddy stubble to protect the environment.

news.title: Seal five properties for tax default, orders Panckhula mayor
news.para: During the meeting, the officials informed the mayor that till now only Rs 39 lakh has been received in the form of building approval plan and development charges from farm houses, houses and showrooms built in the district.

news.title: Assam government plans SIT to probe land records forgery
news.para: The development come after the Guwahati Police recently busted a huge fake land document racket and arrested six persons, including an advocate and government employees, in connection with the case.

news.title: Jaipur development body yet to apply for metro projects' loan
news.para: Urban development and housing (UDH) department officials had claimed that although there were no restrictions on JDA officials to forward files related to loans, they did not do that during the election period.

news.title: Crack down on hotels in Delhi extracting groundwater illegally: NGT
news.para: The Delhi Pollution Control Committee (DPCC) had earlier informed the tribunal that out of the 536 hotels, 257 were illegally extracting groundwater and 185 were doing so under a voluntary disclosure scheme.
